pe=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" | Venue\n! scope=\"col\" | Attendance\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Exhibition Match\n| 18 June <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Hamilton Beats Maritime\n| page =7\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=LII| issue=145\n| date = 1921-06-20\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19210620.2.90\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n|| Hamilton|| 19 || Maritime || 16 || Hamilton\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Exhibition Match\n| 13 Aug <ref>{{cite news\n| title =City Rovers V Cambridge\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17860\n| date = 1921-08-15\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210815.2.98.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n|| Cambridge|| 16 || City Rovers || 14 || Victoria Square, Cambridge\n|-\n|}\n\n==Auckland Representative Fixtures==\nIt was a very busy season for the [[Auckland rugby league team|Auckland]] representative team with ten matches played. Though in reality B and C teams played some of the fixtures as matches were played at the same time in different centres. They won seven matches and lost three. On 20 August Auckland played three matches, which showed off their depth. One at [[Carlaw Park]] versus King Country, one in [[Hamilton, New Zealand|Hamilton]] against [[Waikato rugby league team|South Auckland]], and one against [[Wellington rugby league team|Wellington]] on the [[Basin Reserve]]. They won against King Country and [[Wellington rugby league team|Wellington]], with a loss against [[Waikato rugby league team|South Auckland]].\n\n===Auckland v New Zealand===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 21 May\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 16\u201322\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =New Zealand V Auckland/Local Team Defeated\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]\n| date = 1921-05-23\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210523.2.111.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>| away = New Zealand\n| try1 = [[Frank Delgrosso]], [[Thomas McClymont]], Cargill, L Newdick\n| con1 = G Yardley, [[Thomas McClymont]]\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]] 3, [[Jim Sanders (rugby league)|Jim Sanders]],[[Bill Williams (rugby league)|Bill Williams]], [[Harry Tancred|Henry Tancred]]\n| con2 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]\n| pen2 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]\n| stadium = Auckland Domain 1\n| attendance = 11000\n| referee = A Ferguson\n}}\n\n===Northern Union Challenge Cup===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 30 July\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 31\u20138\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Auckland V Wellington/Victory For Local Team/Game Played In Rain\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17848\n| date = 1921-08-01\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210801.2.107.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n| away = Wellington\n| try1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]], [[John Lang (New Zealand rugby league)|John Lang]] 2, [[Bill Stormont]], H Hawkes, [[Bert Avery]] 2\n| con1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = K Thompson, Nicholls\n| con2 =\n| pen2 = J Kruse\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 6000\n| referee = W Murray\n}}\n\n===Northern Union Challenge Cup===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 6 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 18\u20133\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Representative Match/Auckland Beats Hawke\u2019s Bay/Fast Game On Wet Ground\n| page =3\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXIII| issue=17854\n| date = 1921-08-08\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210808.2.18\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n| away = Hawkes Bay\n| try1 = [[Eric Grey]], [[Charles Woolley (rugby league)|Charles Woolley]], H Hawkes, [[Bert Avery]]\n| con1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]] 3\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = A Atkins\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 6500\n| referee = A Ferguson\n}}\n\n===Auckland v King Country===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 20 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 58\u201325\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =King Country V Auckland/The Visitors Outclassed\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17866\n| date = 1921-08-22\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210822.2.92.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n| away = King Country\n| try1 = [[Wally Somers]] 3, [[Charles Woolley (rugby league)|Charles Woolley]], [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]], [[Bert Avery]] 5, [[Thomas McClymont]] 3, [[Arthur Singe]]\n| con1 = [[Wally Somers]], [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]] 2, [[Thomas McClymont]] 3, [[Eric Grey]], [[Arthur Singe]]\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Lyall 2, Wallace 2, Jumbo\n| con2 = Cribb, Henry 3\n| pen2 = Henry\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 4000\n| referee = W Murray\n}}\n\n===South Auckland (Waikato) v Auckland===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 20 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = South Auckland (Waikato)\n| score = 13\u20133\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Match At Hamilton/Win For South Auckland\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17866\n| date = 1921-08-22\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210822.2.92.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n| away = Auckland\n| try1 = Hemmingway 2, Wilson\n| con1 = G Dufty\n| pen1 = G Dufty\n| try2 = [[George Paki]]\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Hamilton Showgrounds\n| attendance = 2000\n| referee = T Smith\n}}\n\n===Wellington v Auckland===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 20 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Wellington\n| score = 21\u201323\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Auckland V Wellington/Margin Of Two Points\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17866\n| date = 1921-08-22\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210822.2.92.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n| away = Auckland\n| try1 = Hodges, J Shanahan 2\n| con1 = Nicholls 2\n| pen1 = Nicholls 2 (and 1 mark), Balks\n| try2 = [[Ivan Littlewood]], T Peckham, W McNeil, [[Bill Stormont]], H Hawkes\n| con2 = W Flynn 3, [[Bill Stormont]]\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Basin Reserve, Wellington\n| attendance =\n| referee = C Snow\n}}\n\n===West Coast v Auckland===\nNo full team lists were published for this match and none of the scorers were listed either in match reports from any newspaper in New Zealand. The match report did however mention that the following players for Auckland performed well: [[Maurice Wetherill]], W Flynn, G Yardley, T Peckham, V Thomas, and [[Bill Stormont]]. It is most likely that Auckland fielded the same touring team that played in Wellington 4 days prior and in Christchurch 3 days later.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 24 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = West Coast\n| score = 7\u201347\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Auckland V West Coast/An Easy Victory\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17869\n| date = 1921-09-25\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210825.2.105.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>| away = Auckland\n| try1 = Unknown x 11\n| con1 = Unknown x 7\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Unknown x 1\n| con2 = Unknown x 1\n| pen2 = Unknown x 1\n| stadium = Greymouth\n| attendance =\n| referee =\n}}\n\n===Canterbury v Auckland===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 27 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Canterbury\n| score = 14\u201339\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Auckland V Canterbury/Win For Northerners/Thirty-Nine To Fourteen\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17872\n| date = 1921-08-29\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210829.2.93.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n| away = Auckland\n| try1 = W Green, [[Jim Sanders (rugby league)|Jim Sanders]], R Watts, W Healey\n| con1 = [[Jim Sanders (rugby league)|Jim Sanders]]\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = [[Ben Davidson (rugby league)|Ben Davidson]] 2, J McGregor, G Yardley, [[Maurice Wetherill]], C James, [[Bill Stormont]], H Hawkes 2\n| con2 = Mike Flynn 5, T Peckham\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Sydenham Park, Christchurch\n| attendance = 5000\n| referee = A Morris\n}}\n\n===Hawkes Bay v Auckland B===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 27 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Hakes Bay\n| score = 18\u201315\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Hawke\u2019s Bay V Auckland/A Close Contest\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17872\n| date = 1921-08-29\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210829.2.93.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n| away = Auckland B\n| try1 = Douglas, Gibson 2, McCarthy\n| con1 = Exeter\n| pen1 = McCarthy, Exeter\n| try2 = Gallagher 2, S Delaney\n| con2 = [[Craddock Dufty]]\n| pen2 = [[Craddock Dufty]] 2\n| stadium = Napier\n| attendance =\n| referee =\n}}\n\n===Auckland v South Auckland (Waikato)===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 17 September\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 35\u201313\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Auckland V South Auckland/Victory For Local Team/Fast Spectacular Play\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17890\n| date = 1921-09-19\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210919.2.105.2\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n| away = South Auckland (Waikato)\n| try1 = [[Ben Davidson (rugby league)|Ben Davidson]] 4, [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]], H Hawkes 2, [[Bert Avery]], [[George Paki]]\n| con1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]] 4\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = L Stewart, H Manning, S Neill\n| con2 = [[Wilson Hall (New Zealand rugby league)|A. Wilson-Hall]]\n| pen2 = [[Wilson Hall (New Zealand rugby league)|A. Wilson-Hall]]\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 5500\n| referee =\n}}\n\n===Auckland Representative Matches Played and Scorers===\nThere was no scoring for the West Coast match where Auckland won by 47 points to 7. [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]] led Auckland in scoring with 40 points from 6 tries and 11 conversions.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!No!!Name!!Club Team!!Play!!Tries!!Con!!Pen!!Points\n|-\n|1||[[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]||City Rovers||4||6||11||0||40\n|-\n|2||[[Bert Avery]]||Marist Old Boys||4||9||0||0||27\n|-\n|3||H Hawkes||City Rovers||5||7||0||0||21\n|-\n|4||[[Thomas McClymont]]||Ponsonby United||4||4||4||0||20\n|-\n|5||[[Ben Davidson (rugby league)|Ben Davidson]]||City Rovers||4||6||0||0||18\n|-\n|6||M Flynn||Maritime||6||0||8||0||16\n|-\n|7||[[Bill Stormont]]||Marist Old Boys||5||3||1||0||11\n|-\n|7||[[Wally Somers]]||Newton||2||3||1||0||11\n|-\n|9||[[Charles Woolley (rugby league)|Charles Woolley]]||Fire Brigade||5||2||0||0||6\n|-\n|9||[[John Lang (New Zealand rugby league)|John Lang]]||Maritime||4||2||0||0||6\n|-\n|9||[[George Paki]]||City Rovers||2||2||0||0||6\n|-\n|12||G Yardley||Maritime||4||1||1||0||5\n|-\n|12||T Peckham||City Rovers||4||1||1||0||5\n|-\n|12||[[Arthur Singe]]||Marist Old Boys||4||1||1||0||5\n|-\n|12||[[Eric Grey]]||Maritime||4||1||1||0||5\n|-\n|16||[[Frank Delgrosso]]||Ponsonby United||2||1||0||0||3\n|-\n|16||[[Maurice Wetherill]]||City Rovers||7||1||0||0||3\n|-\n|16||G Cargill||Marist Old Boys||3||1||0||0||3\n|-\n|16||L Newdick||Newton Rangers||1||1||0||0||3\n|-\n|16||[[Ivan Littlewood]]||Maritime||1||1||0||0||3\n|-\n|16||M McNeil||Ponsonby United||2||1||0||0||3\n|-\n|16||C James||Newton Rangers||2||1||0||0||3\n|-\n|16||J McGregor||Maritime||2||1||0||0||3\n|-\n|24||[[Sam Lowrie]]||Ponsonby United||3||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|24||W Williams||Newton Rangers||3||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|24||H Wynn||Devonport United||2||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|24||V Thomas||City Rovers||2||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|24||P Gallagher||Marist Old Boys||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|24||Nelson||Devonport United||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|24||[[Nelson Bass]]||Newton Rangers||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|24||J Hing||Marist Old Boys||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|24||Joe Meadows||Ponsonby United||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|24||[[Bill Walsh (rugby league)|Bill Walsh]]||Ponsonby United||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|24||[[Craddock Dufty]]||Newton Rangers||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|24||G Mormon||Ponsonby United||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|24||J Price||Devonport United||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|24||S Delaney||Newton Rangers||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|24||Billy Ghent||Marist Old Boys||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|24||M Clark||?||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|24||F Turner||Marist Old Boys||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|24||N Ballantyne||Maritime||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|24||Charles Webb||Devonport United||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|24||[[Alf Townsend]]||City Rovers||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|24||A Eustace||Marist Old Boys||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|}\n\n== New Zealand Representatives from Auckland ==\nTeam to tour Australia\n\n'''Backs'''\n* [[Eric Grey]] (Maritime)\n* [[Charles Woolley (rugby league)|Charles Woolley]] (Fire Brigade)\n* [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]] (City Rovers)\n* [[Bert Laing]] (City Rovers)\n* [[Clarrie Polson]] (Newton Rangers)\n\n'''Forwards'''\n* [[Wally Somers]] (Newton Rangers)\n* [[Bill Williams (rugby league)|Bill Williams]] (Newton Rangers)\n* [[Harry Tancred|Henry Tancred]] (City Rovers)\n* [[George Paki]] (City Rovers)\n* [[Joe Meadows]] (Ponsonby)\n* [[Bert Avery]] (Maritime)\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.aucklandleague.co.nz/ Auckland Rugby League Official Site]\n\n|}\n\n[[Category:Auckland Rugby League seasons]]\n[[Category:1921 in New Zealand rugby league|Auckland Rugby League]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\nThe 1921 season of [[Auckland Rugby League]] was its 13th. Seventy two teams played across its six main grades.<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Activities in Auckland/Review of Last Season\n| page =9\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LIX| issue=18050\n| date = 1921-03-27\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19220327.2.127.7\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>\n\nThe first grade competition featured seven teams, [[City Rovers]], [[Marist Saints|Marist Old Boys]], [[Maritime (rugby league)|Maritime]], [[North Shore Albions|Devonport]], [[Grafton Athletic|Fire Brigade]] (formerly Grafton Athletic), [[Newton Rangers]], and [[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby United]]. [[City Rovers]] comfortably won the senior championship for the 4th time with a 8 win, 1 draw, 0 loss record ahead of Maritime who were unable to repeat their title win from the previous season. [[City Rovers|City]] had previously won the title in 1910, 1911, and 1916. This was to be the first of 3 consecutive titles for them. They also won the Roope Rooster knockout competition for the 3rd time after previous wins in 1916 and 1918.\n\n== Club Name Changes and Mergers ==\nOn 13 April the Management Committee of the Auckland Rugby League met. At the meeting Grafton was granted permission to change its name to \u201cFire Brigade Club\u201d. [[North Shore Albions|Devonport United]] notified the league that the Devonport Borough Council had allocated the [[Devonport Domain]] for its use. During the season the club was named \u2018North Shore\u2019 and \u2018Devonport\u2019 interchangeably by both ''[[The New Zealand Herald]]'' and the ''[[Auckland Star]]''. In 1920 the club had seen a merger between [[North Shore Albions]] and the Sunnyside club and agreed on the name [[North Shore Albions|Devonport United]] but it appears that the stronger club\u2019s name was still more favoured by those reporting on the games, and it was eventually the name adopted by the club. While the Kingsland Rovers club wrote asking for advice on what it should do regarding a ground for the club to play at.<ref>{{cite news\n| title = The Management Committee\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17755\n| date = 1921-03-14 |page=7\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210414.2.103.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-22}}</ref>\n\n== Carlaw Park Open for Business ==\nHistory was made on 25 June when the first ever match was played on [[Carlaw Park]] between [[City Rovers]] and Maritime. The match was won by [[City Rovers]] 10 points to 8. Prior to the match an official opening ceremony was held. \u201cThe park was declared open by Hon. [[Arthur Myers]], MP. Mr and Mrs. Carlaw were each presented with a gold badge and certificate of life membership on the ground, and at the conclusion of the ceremony Mrs Carlaw kicked off for the first game on the new park\u201d.<ref>{{cite news\n| title =City Defeats Maritime At Carlaw Park/Exciting Contest Witnessed\n| page =8\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=LII| issue=151\n| date = 1921-06-27\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19210627.2.112\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref> [[City Rovers]] capped a remarkable season by winning the [[Thacker Shield]] from [[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby United]] on the final day of the season after having already won the Monteith Shield by winning the First Grade Championship, and the Roope Rooster Knock-out trophy.\n\n==Female Football Club Denied By the League==\nOn 12 July a meeting was held in Parnell to form a \"girls\" rugby league competition and over 40 enrolling. They were to play a game on Carlaw Park on the following Saturday afternoon. They were all aged between 16 and 20 years of age. The chairman of the Parnell club, Mr. A. R. Turner explained \"that it wished to develop the girls as well as the men, and to this end the club was being formed at the suggestion of the girls\". A trophy \"similar to the Monteith Shield\" had been donated, and \"members of the Auckland League Management Committee had donated a football, and were providing assistance in supplying jerseys. At the meeting when the time for enrollment came it was described that \"they rose in a body and fairly rushed the table, which was in danger of being overturned in the excitement of the moment\" Ivan Culpan, secretary of the league told the girls that the league would train them every evening in the lead up to the match.<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Girl Footballers/League Club Formed/First Match on Saturday/Much Enthusiasm Shown\n| page =9\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17832\n| date = 1921-07-13\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210713.2.104\n| accessdate = 2020-02-29}}</ref> Over the next week the number of girls enrolled increased to 65. It later transpired that the members of the Auckland Rugby League who had attended had done so by invitation and were not necessarily acting on behalf of the league with the comments they had made. At the Auckland Rugby league Management meeting the following night the decision on whether to support the girls playing and affiliate the club with the league was deferred. Both G. Hunt and [[Ted Phelan|E Phelan]] spoke against allowing the girls to play.<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Girl FootballClub/Question of Affiliation/League Defers Decision/Matter of Physical Welfare\n| page =9\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17833 \n| date = 1921-07-14\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210714.2.111\n| accessdate = 2020-02-29}}</ref> And at a meeting on 20 July the Auckland Rugby League decided to oppose the girls playing football. Mr. J. Carlaw said that medical opinion was in opposition to females playing the sport. Mr Stallworthy and Mr. E Feilding suggested a trial game with modified rules take place with doctors watching but the request was declined.<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Girl Footballers\n| page =7\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=LII| issue=172 \n| date = 1921-07-21\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19210721.2.93\n| accessdate = 2020-02-29}}</ref>\n\n{{s-start}}\n    {{s-bef|before=[[1920 Auckland Rugby League season|1920]]}}\n    {{s-ttl|title=13th [[Auckland Rugby League]] season\n    |years=1921}}\n    {{s-aft|after=[[1922 Auckland Rugby League season|1922]]}}\n    {{end}}\n\n== Monteith Shield (First Grade Championship) ==\n=== Final Standings ===\n{|\n|-\n|\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!width=175 |Team\n!width=20 abbr=\"Played\" |Pld\n!width=20 abbr=\"Won\" |W\n!width=20 abbr=\"Drawn\" |D\n!width=20 abbr=\"Lost\" |L\n!width=20 abbr=\"For\" |F\n!width=20 abbr=\"Against\" |A\n!width=20 abbr=\"Points\" |Pts\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[City Rovers]]\n|9||8||1||0||250||50||'''17'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Maritime (rugby league)|Maritime]]\n|9||6||0||3||135||112||'''12'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Marist Saints|Marist Old Boys]]\n|9||5||0||4||167||122||'''10'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby United]]\n|9||5||0||4||138||99||'''10'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Newton Rangers]]\n|9||3||1||5||83||129||'''7'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[North Shore Albions|Devonport United]]\n|7||1||0||6||61||132||'''2'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Grafton Athletic|Fire Brigade]]\n|8||1||0||7||49||179||'''2'''\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Monteith Shield Fixtures ===\n\n===Round 1===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 23 April\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 22\u20135\n| report = <ref name=\"autoRefA\">{{cite news\n| title =Opening of the Season\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17764\n| date = 1921-04-25\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210425.2.110.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-22}}</ref>\n| away = Marist\n| try1 = [[Alf Townsend]], [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]], [[Bert Laing]], H Hawkes\n| con1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]] 4\n| pen1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]\n| try2 = [[Bill Stormont]]\n| con2 =\n| pen2 = [[Bill Stormont]] 1 mark\n| stadium = Victoria Park 1\n| attendance = 6000\n| referee = W Murray\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 23 April\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Devonport\n| score = 3\u20132\n| r