921 if you include the Sixth Grade which was split into an A and B grade, and the cadet competition. Clubs with only lower grade teams were:\n\nGrades were made of the following teams with the winning team in bold:\n*'''Second Grade''': Maritime, '''Newton''', Otahuhu, Ellerslie, City Rovers, Ponsonby, Manukau, Marist Old Boys. Newton defeated Maritime in the Second Grade final by 17 points to 11 at Carlaw Park to win the Second Grade Cup.<ref name=\"autoRefC\">{{cite news\n| title =Junior Championship Final/Newton Defeats Maritime\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17896\n| date = 1921-09-26\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210926.2.115.2\n| accessdate = 2019-08-26}}</ref>\n*'''Third Grade''' (Myers Cup): Point Chevalier, North Shore, '''Kingsland''', Ponsonby, Ellerslie, Newton.\n*'''Fourth Grade''': City Rovers, City Rovers B, Kingsland, Manukau, Point Chevalier, Richmond, Maritime, Otahuhu, Ponsonby, and Takapuna.\n*'''Fifth Grade''': Manukau, Northcote, Otahuhu, Ponsonby, Richmond, Maritime A, '''City Rovers''', Maritime B, Manukau, Northcote, North Shore, Marist Old Boys, Takapuna. City Rovers defeated Richmond by 5 points to 2 to win the championship.<ref name=\"autoRefC\" />\n*'''Sixth Grade''': Ponsonby United, Ellerslie, Otahuhu, Kingsland B, Otahuhu A, Kingsland A, City Rovers A, Takapuna, Marist Old Boys, '''Richmond''', Manukau, Maritime, Ellerslie B, Marist Old Boys B\n*'''Sixth Grade B''': Richmond, Maritime, Marist Old Boys, Ellerslie, and '''Ponsonby United'''.\n*'''Cadet Competition''': Senior Cadets 13th Company A, '''Senior Cadets 18th Company''', 24th Company, Senior 4th Company, Senior Cadets 13th Company B, 51st Senior Cadets Company (Devonport), 23rd Company, 37 Company, 34th Senior Cadets Company (Mt Eden). This competition was won by the 18th Company of Senior Cadets after they won the final game of the season defeating the 13th Company by 7 points to 2.\n\n=== Challenge Shield ===\nThe Thacker Shield was held by [[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby United]] coming into the 1921 season however there was a dispute over whether the shield should be held by North Island teams as it was unclear if it had been intended for competition amoung South Island teams only. The New Zealand council decided that the rules should be amended to allow North Island teams to hold it but the donor, Dr. H. T.J. Thacker and the Canterbury Rugby League would not agree to them. As such the shield was returned to the donor. Mr. C Weaver donated a trophy to take its place and this became known as the Challenge Shield and it was this that Ponsonby went on to defend twice. They first hosted [[Petone Panthers|Petone]] from [[Wellington]] who they beat 18\u201313. In the curtain-raiser [[Petone Panthers|Petone juniors]] were defeated by [[Richmond Bulldogs|Richmond]] by 14 points to 8. In the evening the Petone players were entertained at the Druids\u2019 Hall by the [[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby]] club and [[Auckland Rugby League|Auckland League]]. They later defeated Huntly 19\u20138 before losing the Shield to local rivals [[City Rovers]]\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 10 September\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Ponsonby\n| score = 18\u201313\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Thacker Shield Match/Ponsonby Retains Trophy/Petone Defeated By 5 Points\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17884\n| date = 1921-09-12\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210912.2.118.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-26}}</ref>| away = Petone\n| try1 = E McGregor 2, Southernwood, [[Dougie McGregor]]\n| con1 = [[Dougie McGregor]] 3\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = [[Horace Nunn]], Shanahan 2\n| con2 = Balks\n| pen2 = Nicholls\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 7000\n| referee = W Murray\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 8 October\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Ponsonby\n| score = 19\u20138\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Thacker Shield Match/Ponsonby V Huntly/Win For the Local Team\n| page =3\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17908\n| date = 1921-10-10\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19211010.2.15.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n| away = Huntly\n| try1 = [[Thomas McClymont]], Blackie, W Edwards, W McNeil, J Hing\n| con1 = [[Thomas McClymont]] 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = B Paki, Peckham\n| con2 =\n| pen2 = J Raynor\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 2000\n| referee = A Ferguson\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 15 October\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 25\u201310\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Final Game of Season/Thacker Shield Match/City Defeat Ponsonby\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17914\n| date = 1921-10-17\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19211017.2.129.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n| away = Ponsonby\n| try1 = [[George Paki]], [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]], Peckham, [[Ben Davidson (rugby league)|Ben Davidson]], H Hawkes\n| con1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]] 4\n| pen1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]\n| try2 = G Mormon, [[Dougie McGregor]]\n| con2 = [[Dougie McGregor]], [[Frank Delgrosso]]\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 7500\n| referee = Len Farrant\n}}\n\n=== Exhibition Matches ===\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible\"\n|+ class=\"nowrap\" | List of Exhibition Matches\n|-\n|\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" |\n! scope=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" |\n! scope=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" | Venue\n! scope=\"col\" | Attendance\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Exhibition Match\n| 18 June <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Hamilton Beats Maritime\n| page =7\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=LII| issue=145\n| date = 1921-06-20\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19210620.2.90\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n|| Hamilton|| 19 || Maritime || 16 || Hamilton\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Exhibition Match\n| 13 Aug <ref>{{cite news\n| title =City Rovers V Cambridge\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17860\n| date = 1921-08-15\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210815.2.98.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n|| Cambridge|| 16 || City Rovers || 14 || Victoria Square, Cambridge\n|-\n|}\n\n==Auckland Representative Fixtures==\nIt was a very busy season for the [[Auckland rugby league team|Auckland]] representative team with ten matches played. Though in reality B and C teams played some of the fixtures as matches were played at the same time in different centres. They won seven matches and lost three. On 20 August Auckland played three matches, which showed off their depth. One at [[Carlaw Park]] versus King Country, one in [[Hamilton, New Zealand|Hamilton]] against [[Waikato rugby league team|South Auckland]], and one against [[Wellington rugby league team|Wellington]] on the [[Basin Reserve]]. They won against King Country and [[Wellington rugby league team|Wellington]], with a loss against [[Waikato rugby league team|South Auckland]].\n\n===Auckland v New Zealand===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 21 May\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 16\u201322\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =New Zealand V Auckland/Local Team Defeated\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]\n| date = 1921-05-23\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210523.2.111.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>| away = New Zealand\n| try1 = [[Frank Delgrosso]], [[Thomas McClymont]], Cargill, L Newdick\n| con1 = G Yardley, [[Thomas McClymont]]\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]] 3, [[Jim Sanders (rugby league)|Jim Sanders]],[[Bill Williams (rugby league)|Bill Williams]], [[Harry Tancred|Henry Tancred]]\n| con2 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]\n| pen2 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]\n| stadium = Auckland Domain 1\n| attendance = 11000\n| referee = A Ferguson\n}}\n\n===Northern Union Challenge Cup===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 30 July\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 31\u20138\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Auckland V Wellington/Victory For Local Team/Game Played In Rain\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17848\n| date = 1921-08-01\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210801.2.107.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n| away = Wellington\n| try1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]], [[John Lang (New Zealand rugby league)|John Lang]] 2, [[Bill Stormont]], H Hawkes, [[Bert Avery]] 2\n| con1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = K Thompson, Nicholls\n| con2 =\n| pen2 = J Kruse\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 6000\n| referee = W Murray\n}}\n\n===Northern Union Challenge Cup===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 6 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 18\u20133\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Representative Match/Auckland Beats Hawke\u2019s Bay/Fast Game On Wet Ground\n| page =3\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXIII| issue=17854\n| date = 1921-08-08\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210808.2.18\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n| away = Hawkes Bay\n| try1 = [[Eric Grey]], [[Charles Woolley (rugby league)|Charles Woolley]], H Hawkes, [[Bert Avery]]\n| con1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]] 3\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = A Atkins\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 6500\n| referee = A Ferguson\n}}\n\n===Auckland v King Country===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 20 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 58\u201325\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =King Country V Auckland/The Visitors Outclassed\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17866\n| date = 1921-08-22\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210822.2.92.1\n| accessdate =