 none of the scorers were listed either in match reports from any newspaper in New Zealand. The match report did however mention that the following players for Auckland performed well: [[Maurice Wetherill]], W Flynn, G Yardley, T Peckham, V Thomas, and [[Bill Stormont]]. It is most likely that Auckland fielded the same touring team that played in Wellington 4 days prior and in Christchurch 3 days later.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 24 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = West Coast\n| score = 7\u201347\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Auckland V West Coast/An Easy Victory\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17869\n| date = 1921-09-25\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210825.2.105.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>| away = Auckland\n| try1 = Unknown x 11\n| con1 = Unknown x 7\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Unknown x 1\n| con2 = Unknown x 1\n| pen2 = Unknown x 1\n| stadium = Greymouth\n| attendance =\n| referee =\n}}\n\n===Canterbury v Auckland===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 27 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Canterbury\n| score = 14\u201339\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Auckland V Canterbury/Win For Northerners/Thirty-Nine To Fourteen\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17872\n| date = 1921-08-29\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210829.2.93.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n| away = Auckland\n| try1 = W Green, [[Jim Sanders (rugby league)|Jim Sanders]], R Watts, W Healey\n| con1 = [[Jim Sanders (rugby league)|Jim Sanders]]\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = [[Ben Davidson (rugby league)|Ben Davidson]] 2, J McGregor, G Yardley, [[Maurice Wetherill]], C James, [[Bill Stormont]], H Hawkes 2\n| con2 = Mike Flynn 5, T Peckham\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Sydenham Park, Christchurch\n| attendance = 5000\n| referee = A Morris\n}}\n\n===Hawkes Bay v Auckland B===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 27 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Hakes Bay\n| score = 18\u201315\n| repor