aca\n*Channel 10 (RF channel 36): [[K36PU-D]] - ([[PBS]]/[[Create (TV network)|Create]]/[[PBS Kids]]) - Pioche\n*Channel 10 (RF channel 36): [[K36OF-D]] - ([[PBS]]/[[Create (TV network)|Create]]/[[PBS Kids]]) - Ursine\n*Channel 11 (RF channel 32): [[K32NW-D]] - ([[Fox Broadcasting Corporation|FOX]]/[[Charge! (TV network)|Charge!]]/[[Antenna TV]]) - Mina/Luning\n*Channel 11 (RF channel 18): [[K42EK-D]] - ([[Fox Broadcasting Corporation|FOX]]/[[Charge! (TV network)|Charge!]]/[[Antenna TV]]) - Round Mountain\n*Channel 13 (RF channel 20): [[K44JR-D]] - ([[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]/[[Laff (TV network)|Laff]]/[[Grit (TV network)|Grit]]) - Laughlin\n*Channel 13 (RF channel 31): [[K42AA-D]] - ([[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]/[[Laff (TV network)|Laff]]/[[Grit (TV network)|Grit]]) - Pahrump\n*Channel 21 (RF channel 27): [[K27OI-D]] - ([[MyNetworkTV]]/Nevada Sports Net/[[Stadium (sports network)|Stadium]]/[[Comet (TV network)|Comet TV]]) - Mina/Luning\n\n==Local cable channels (Las Vegas Area)==\n*Channel 2: KCLV - City of Las Vegas\n*Channel 4: CCTV - Clark County also available as streaming video\n*Channel 19: [[Las Vegas One]], a joint project between [[Cox Cable]], KLAS-TV and [[The Greenspun Corporation]] (Ceased Operation)\n*Channel 3: KLBC - tv2KLBC \n\n{{NAmerTV}}\n{{Nevada}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of television channels in the United States|Nevada]]\n[[Category:Television stations in Nevada| ]]\n[[Category:Nevada-related lists|Television stations]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThis is a '''list of broadcast television stations''' serving cities in the U.S. state of [[Nevada]].\n\n==Full-power stations==\n'''VC''' refers to the station's [[PSIP]] [[virtual channel]]. '''RF''' refers to the station's physical RF channel.\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse\"\n! '''Area served'''